content:
Manage a prediction definition and its associated models.

To view a prediction definition:

Open Model Manager.
Click the name of the prediction definition you want to view, or click View in the dropdown.
A graph shows a timeline of total predictions with a date range selector.
A list of models associated with this prediction definition is shown.
Settings are displayed for configuring automated prediction writeback, model refresh, and quality notifications.

To set up performance monitoring, see Configure Performance Monitoring for a Prediction Definition.

The settings panel includes:
Prediction ID: Unique system-assigned ID for the prediction definition.
Developer Name: Name of the developer associated with this prediction definition.
Create Tableau Table Calculation: Click to create a table calculation snippet for Tableau.
title: Understanding Salesforce Prediction Definitions
